{{Italic title}}
'''''Architectura: Zeitschrift für Geschichte der Baukunst''''' is a biannual [[peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] of the [[history of architecture]] published by [[Deutscher Kunstverlag]]. The journal was established in 1971 and is abstracted and indexed in the [[Arts and Humanities Citation Index]],<ref name=ISI>{{cite web |url=http://ip-science.thomsonreuters.com/mjl/ |title=Master Journal List |publisher=[[Thomson Reuters]] |work=Intellectual Property & Science |accessdate=2015-05-06}}</ref> [[Art Abstracts]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ebscohost.com/titleLists/aax-coverage.htm |title=Database Coverage List |publisher=[[EBSCO Information Services]] |work=Art Abstracts |accessdate=2015-05-06}}</ref> [[Art Index]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ebscohost.com/titleLists/aai-coverage.htm |title=Database Coverage List |publisher=[[EBSCO Information Services]] |work=Art Index |accessdate=2015-05-06}}</ref> and [[Current Contents]]/Arts & Humanities.<ref name=ISI/> Articles are in German or English. The [[editors-in-chief]] are Dorothée Sack and Johannes Cramer ([[Technical University of Berlin]]).

