{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2012}} {{Infobox artist | image = The_stars_and_the_starfish.jpg | caption = "The Stars and the Starfish" | name = Bleeps.gr | birth_place = [[Athens]], [[Greece]] | nationality = Greek | field = [[Street art]], [[artivism]], [[Social commentary]] | website = {{URL|http://www.bleeps.gr}} }}
'''Bleeps.gr''' (or '''Bleeps''') is the pseudonym used by '''M.V. Kakouris''', who is a [[Greeks|Greek]] artist. Bleeps creates political [[street art]], [[paintings]] and [[installation art|installations]];<ref>Helena Celdrán (7 July 2011), [http://www.20minutos.es/noticia/1102588/0/bleeps/grecia/arte-callejero/ "Aquiles también sale a protestar a las calles de Grecia"], 20minutos.es.</ref> he is involved with the [[artivism]] movement.<ref name="Greece Germany relations">{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2011/10/26/us-greece-germany-relations-idUSTRE79P3LN20111026|title=Greece Germany relations|publisher=The Reuters|last=Ferris-Rotman|first=Amie|accessdate=26 October 2011|date=26 October 2011}}</ref> Most of his works can be seen in [[Athens]], but a number of others can be found in cities and rural areas around [[Greece]] and Europe.<ref name="in Athens art blossoms amid debt crisis">{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2011/10/15/arts/in-athens-art-blossoms-amid-debt-crisis.html?_r=3&pagewanted=1&sq=greece&st=cse&scp=4|title=In Athens art blossoms amid debt crisis|work=The New York Times|last=Donadio|first=Rachel|accessdate=14 October 2011|date=14 October 2011}}</ref>
==History== Bleeps started creating street art while he was in [[Bristol]], [[UK]], between 2003 and 2005,<ref name="bleeps.gr beginning">{{cite news|url=http://www.huckmagazine.com/art-and-culture/art-2/street-artist-responding-greeces-social-turmoil/|title=The street artist responding to Greece’s social turmoil|publisher=huckmagazine|last=Ross |first=Alex Robert|date= 8 July 2015}}</ref>where he became familiar with the local underground scene.<ref name="bleeps.gr history">{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-20553444|title=Greece bailout: How the crisis fuels the arts in Athens|publisher=BBC News|last=Lowen|first=Mark|accessdate=2 December 2012|date=2 December 2012}}</ref>
==Style and themes== Most of Bleeps' street art projects derive elements from [[conceptual art]], [[folk art]] and various past art movements, while the protagonists depicted are associated with Bleeps' interpretation of social life.<ref name="bleeps.gr style">{{cite web|url=http://www.zdf.de/ZDFmediathek/beitrag/video/1507266/Griechenlands-Krise-als-Graffiti-Kunst#/beitrag/video/1507266/Griechenlands-Krise-als-Graffiti-Kunst|title=Griechenlands Krise als Graffiti Kunst|publisher=ZDF|last=Jessen|first=Corinna|accessdate=12 January 2011}}</ref>
His stated goal is to examine systemic figures such as religion, politics, monetary system and [[consumerism]].<ref name="bleeps.gr goal">{{cite web|url=http://www.ftd.de/lifestyle/outofoffice/:out-of-office-kunst-kommt-von-kummer/60132276.html|title=Kunst kommt von Kummer|publisher=Financial Times Deutschland|last=Bontrup|first=Hiltrud|accessdate=22 November 2011}}</ref><ref name="bleeps.gr street art">{{cite web|url=http://www.francetv.fr/defense-d-afficher/en/#/bleeps|title=Défense d'afficher|publisher=France TV (An interactive documentary written by Sidonie Garnier, François Le Gall and Jeanne Thibord)|accessdate=19 March 2012}}</ref>
[[File:Sisyphean choice.JPG |thumb|Bleeps' work: part of the windows series]]
==Financial crisis== Since the beginning of the [[Greek financial crisis]] in 2008, Bleeps has been creating a series of works related to the crisis' impact on ordinary people<ref name="bleeps.gr financial crisis">{{cite news | url=http://uk.reuters.com/article/2012/06/15/greece-graffiti-vote-idUKL5E8H790B20120615 | title=Greeks vent election despair through graffiti|publisher=Reuters|last1=Tagaris|first1=Karolina|last2=Osborn|first2=Andrew|accessdate=15 June 2012|date=15 June 2012}}</ref> and the lower middle class, globally and in his country.<ref name="bleeps.gr financial ">{{cite web|url=http://tvthek.orf.at/programs/1310-Report/episodes/4201287-Report-Spezial|title=Report-Spezial|publisher=ORF TV THEK|last=Hafner|first=Patrick|accessdate=18 June 2012}}{{dead link|date=July 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> <ref name="bleeps.gr research Lund University">{{cite web | url=https://lup.lub.lu.se/search/publication/8e81440f-1b97-4832-ac69-3a06568bf502 | title= HOPE WANTED |last=Stampoulidis |first=Georgios |accessdate= 1 January 2016 |pages=66-73}}</ref><ref name="bleeps.gr photo essay">{{cite news | url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/gallery/2011/aug/03/greece-crisis-in-pictures#/?picture=377548531&index=0|title=Greece in Crisis | work=The Guardian|last=Smith|first=Sean|accessdate=3 August 2011|location=London|date=3 August 2011}}</ref><ref name="bleeps.gr crisis art">{{cite web|url=https://www.npr.org/2012/06/16/155169610/greece-prepares-to-give-elections-another-go|title=Voters To Decide Outcome Of Current Greek Drama|publisher=NPR radio|last=Poggioli|first=Sylvia|accessdate=17 June 2012}}</ref>
